  "prompt": "Which book will good for special theory of relativity for JAM PH?",
  "response": "For preparing for the Joint Admission Test for M.Sc. (JAM) in Physics, especially in the topic of Special Theory of Relativity, here are some recommended books:\n\n1. **\"Concepts of Modern Physics\" by Arthur Beiser** - This book provides a clear introduction to the concepts of modern physics, including relativity, and is suitable for undergraduate students.\n\n2. **\"Introduction to Special Relativity\" by Robert Resnick** - A concise and clear exposition of special relativity, this book is very accessible and effectively covers the fundamental concepts.\n\n3. **\"Spacetime Physics\" by Edwin F. Taylor and John Archibald Wheeler** - This book emphasizes the conceptual understanding of relativity and includes plenty of diagrams and examples, making it an excellent resource for students.\n\n4. **\"A First Course in General Relativity\" by Bernard Schutz** - While this book focuses on general relativity, it also provides a solid foundation in special relativity, making it useful for understanding both concepts.\n\n5. **\"Relativity: The Special and the General Theory\" by Albert Einstein** - Written by the original creator of the theories, this book offers a deep insight into his thoughts and is essential reading for anyone interested in relativity.\n\n6. **\"Modern Physics\" by David J. Griffiths** - Known for its clarity and rigor, Griffiths\u2019 book includes chapters on special relativity that are easy to understand and apply.\n\nThese books should provide a strong foundation in special relativity, helping you prepare effectively for the JAM Physics exam. Make sure to also solve problems and practice, as understanding the concepts is crucial for mastering the subject.",
